   <taskbody>
      <prereq class="- topic/section task/prereq ">
         <indexterm class="- topic/indexterm ">HMI</indexterm>
         <note class="- topic/note ">The update of the firmware
on the controller box can be done via a RS232 serial connection.</note>
      </prereq>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Connect your laptop to the service port (J405) located
on the rear side of the front panel (A810).</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <note class="- topic/note ">Use the service port cable 940â€“0024D for the
proper connection of all required signals.</note>
            </stepxmp>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/location_of_service_port_j405_on_the_rear_side_of_the_front_panel_120mm_0000116570.svg"
                         translate="yes"
                         xml:lang="en"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Launch the UPS Tuner and select <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Display Module</uicontrol>. After start-up, your laptop will automatically log in and the main
menu appears on the terminal screen.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <note class="- topic/note ">Navigate through the menu tree by typing the number
of the submenu you wish to enter, followed by the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ENTER</uicontrol> key.</note>
            </stepxmp>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp "/>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Type <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">5</uicontrol> (<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">HMI Firmware
Update</uicontrol>).</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/tunerhmia_0000148864.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Type <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">1</uicontrol> to initialize the HMI for
the firmware update, or press the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ESC</uicontrol> key to
abort. After successful initialization, the HMI waits for a new hex
file.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/tunerhmib_0000148863.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
                  <image href="../Images/tunerhmic_0000148862.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click on <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Send file</uicontrol> and browse to
the firmware file on your laptop and click on <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Open</uicontrol>. </cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/tunerhmid_0000148861.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/tunerhmi1_0000148860.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">After the file transfer, the file checksum will now appear
on the screen. Check if file checksum is correct before continuing.
If the file checksum is not correct, press the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ESC</uicontrol> key.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/tunerhmi2_0000148859.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Type <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">y</uicontrol> to confirm the update and
copy the new firmware from the SRAM to the FLASH memory.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <note class="- topic/note ">If you wish to cancel the update and keep the old firmware,
press the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">ESC</uicontrol> key.</note>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">After the firmware has been successfully updated and <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Update done. Restart system...</uicontrol> appears on the screen,
restart the HMI by either unplugging the HMI supply or switch the
system off and then back on.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/tunerhmi4_0000148858.jpg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
      </steps>
